# Images Directory

This directory contains images used in the Task Lifecycle Dashboard documentation.

## Image Files

### Dashboard Screenshots
- `dashboard-overview.png` - Main dashboard view showing all active tasks
- `task-creation.png` - Screenshot of the task creation form
- `task-details.png` - Detailed view of a single task
- `task-editing.png` - Task editing interface
- `task-filters.png` - Task filtering and search options

### Workflow Diagrams
- `task-lifecycle-flow.png` - Visual representation of task states and transitions
- `user-workflow.png` - Step-by-step user interaction flow
- `system-architecture.png` - High-level system architecture diagram

### UI Components
- `buttons-states.png` - Various button states (normal, hover, disabled)
- `form-elements.png` - Input fields, dropdowns, and other form controls
- `navigation-menu.png` - Main navigation menu structure
- `status-indicators.png` - Task status badges and icons

### Tutorial Screenshots
- `getting-started-1.png` - First step of the getting started guide
- `getting-started-2.png` - Second step of the getting started guide
- `getting-started-3.png` - Third step of the getting started guide

## Image Guidelines

- All screenshots should be taken at 1920x1080 resolution
- Use PNG format for screenshots with UI elements
- Use JPG format for photographs or complex images
- Compress images to keep file sizes reasonable (under 500KB when possible)
- Use descriptive filenames with hyphens instead of spaces
- Include alt text descriptions when referencing images in documentation

## Adding New Images

When adding new images to this directory:

1. Follow the naming convention: `category-description.extension`
2. Update this README file with the new image information
3. Ensure images are optimized for web display
4. Test that images display correctly in the documentation